wikipedia_page.main: Colonel Edward Corbett (30 December 1817 – 6 January 1895) was a British land-owner and Conservative Party politician from an old Norman family in Shropshire. He held a seat in the House of Commons from 1868 to 1877.

response: * Edward Corbett (politician) (1817–1895), MP for South Shropshire 1868–77
His oldest surviving son Edward Corbett (1817–1895) was MP for South Shropshire from 1868 to 1877.
